Two persons died in an accident at Nawfia along Awka-Enugu expressway in Anambra State. The crash involved a Mercedes 911 truck and Toyota Highlander SUV with four persons on board.   ASUU: of slaves and slave drivers     Same old tale     The right to know   An eyewitness said the Highlander driver wrongfully  overtook the truck, nearly ramming into the truck. “The truck driver veered off the road while trying to dodge the Highlander and fell on its side with two of his passengers trapped under the truck,” he said. Sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Adeoye Irelewuyi confirmed the incident, blaming the crash on wrongful overtaking. SPONSORED